# Project Command: /exec-review-polish

## Command Definition
**Name:** `/exec-review-polish`
**Type:** Project command (scoped to this Tech Glossary project)
**Purpose:** Review and polish code for PM-focused styling, clarity, and accessibility

## Command Instructions

When `/exec-review-polish` is invoked, perform the following review and improvements:

### 1. Code Clarity & Readability
- Review code for clarity and maintainability
- Ensure consistent naming conventions
- Add helpful comments where needed
- Verify semantic HTML structure
- Check TypeScript types are properly defined

### 2. Styling & Visual Polish
- Review CSS for consistency and maintainability
- Ensure proper spacing and visual hierarchy
- Verify responsive design considerations
- Check color contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum)
- Ensure consistent styling patterns

### 3. Accessibility (A11y)
- Verify semantic HTML elements are used correctly
- Check ARIA labels and roles where appropriate
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly
- Verify focus states are visible
- Check color contrast meets accessibility standards
- Ensure text is readable and properly sized

### 4. PM-Focused Improvements
- Ensure UI is clear and intuitive
- Verify information hierarchy is logical
- Check that content is scannable and digestible
- Ensure consistent visual language
- Verify user experience is smooth and polished

### 5. Code Quality
- Check for any linting errors
- Verify TypeScript compilation succeeds
- Ensure code follows best practices
- Check for potential bugs or issues
- Verify browser compatibility considerations

### 6. Documentation
- Ensure code is self-documenting
- Verify README is up to date if needed
- Check that comments explain "why" not just "what"

## Output Format
When executing this command, provide:
1. A summary of issues found
2. Specific recommendations for improvements
3. Code changes needed (if any)
4. Priority level for each issue (High/Medium/Low)

## Focus Areas for This Project
- Glossary card styling and layout
- Tag styling and accessibility
- Typography and readability
- Color contrast and visual hierarchy
- Responsive design
- TypeScript type safety
- Semantic HTML structure

